    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Vapi Appointment Booking Agent\n\n1. Create a Vapi Assistant at vapi.ai\n2. Add two Custom Tools (Functions): `check_availability` (param: date) and `book_appointment` (params: name, phone, service, date, time)\n3. Set the Server URL for both tools to this workflow's Production Webhook URL (shown on the Webhook node once published)\n4. Connect the \"Notify Business Owner\" Gmail node to your Gmail account (credentials must be added manually)\n5. Publish this workflow (toggle Active) before testing calls",
        "height": 200,
        "width": 300,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "5643f05f-adfa-4fea-9a43-be5cbc098455",
      "name": "Sticky Note 37c7ab5d",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -48,
        -48
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const bookedTimes = $input.all().map(item => item.json.appointmentTime).filter(Boolean);\nconst businessHours = ['09:00','10:00','11:00','12:00','13:00','14:00','15:00','16:00','17:00'];\nconst available = businessHours.filter(t => !bookedTimes.includes(t));\nconst date = $('Parse Tool Call').item.json.date || 'the requested date';\nconst resultText = available.length > 0\n  ? `Available appointment slots on ${date}: ${available.join(', ')}.`\n  : `Sorry, there are no available slots on ${date}. Please try another date.`;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    toolCallId: $('Parse Tool Call').item.json.toolCallId,\n    resultText\n  }\n}];"
      },
      "id": "92c509ed-fffe-4cfc-8889-24a47f15e63f",
      "name": "Compute Available Slots",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
